Functionality -
	Our application will provide a personalized dashboard where users can identify what bank loans they will be approved for. Upon entering the application, a create operation will begin as users will be asked to input their personal information with their financial information to a User’s Financial Information table. This then triggers the read functionality where SQL queries are run to compare the user’s financial profile against historical bank loan data. Stored procedures such as “Join” operations and “Group By” aggregations will be used to achieve the results which are then displayed to the user through a pre-qualification score and a ranked list matching the user with the banks most likely to give them loan approval. This is also where we will be including our second creative component which is the bank approval heatmap which will be using a trigger to monitor the historical data performance table. To ensure the app remains dynamic, we will allow users to update their profile within the Loan Helper/Assistant feature to simulate different financial scenarios and a delete function to clear out any old simulations.
	The workload will be distributed amongst all members of the group so each member is able to play to their strengths, while also getting the opportunity to apply their database knowledge from this course. We will have 2 members primarily focused on working on the frontend and visualization. They will be responsible for the dashboard, search interface, and heatmap visualization. We will then have 2 members primarily focused on working on the backend. Their tasks will be … Finally, as a collective team we will work together on the database aspect of the project. This will include … We believe this split will give everyone on our team a fair opportunity to work on their database skills while also building upon previous strengths.
